The projects that we need to work on that are outside the scope of a budget, absolutely.

831
01:03:27,656 --> 01:03:29,817
And those are the things we have to look at, Mr. President.

832
01:03:30,117 --> 01:03:32,399
And there are other avenues to address those issues.

833
01:03:33,400 --> 01:03:36,222
It's not just looking at a Prop 2.5 override.

834
01:03:37,023 --> 01:03:40,085
You can look at debt exclusion, which is a one-time fixed cost.

835
01:03:41,786 --> 01:03:44,007
for a particular project that needs to be done.

836
01:03:44,027 --> 01:03:48,150
So I'm not saying we should never move ahead on projects that we need to do in the community.

837
01:03:48,470 --> 01:03:50,552
What I'm saying is we have to be mindful.

838
01:03:50,592 --> 01:03:56,896
If we're going to talk about keeping people in their homes and making method affordable, you can't do both.

839
01:03:56,936 --> 01:04:03,500
