1065
01:22:31,984 --> 01:22:32,624
It's important.

1066
01:22:33,424 --> 01:22:34,025
Councilor Knight.

1067
01:22:35,245 --> 01:22:40,667
I think it's important to point out, Mr. President, when we set the tax rate this past year at $9.43 per thousand dollars of valuation for residential properties,

1068
01:22:43,542 --> 01:22:46,584
One thing that we did discuss was the residential property tax exemption.

1069
01:22:47,265 --> 01:22:55,251
And when we went through this exercise in determining whether or not that would be something that was good for the community, I believe what was established was a break-even point of $727,000.

1070
01:22:55,551 --> 01:22:58,673
So any home that was valued over $727,000 that was owner-occupied would not see

1071
01:23:05,452 --> 01:23:11,895
an increase in the tax bill of the percentage that we so chose to apply.

1072
01:23:11,915 --> 01:23:18,958
In fact, what they'd see would be an increase in their tax bill above and beyond what their regular taxation would be without an owner-occupied exemption.

1073
01:23:19,519 --> 01:23:28,123
So there are over 4,000 homes in this community, Mr. President, that are over the $727,000 breakeven point, and over 1,300 of those homes are occupied by individuals that are senior citizens.

1074
01:23:33,105 --> 01:23:41,328
So that is why the Metro City Council, when we set the tax rate, did not adopt the residential exemption, if I remember correctly, Mr. President.

1075
01:23:41,368 --> 01:23:46,409
But I just want to get that out there, because I know Mr. Castagnetti asked why that wasn't adopted.

1076
01:23:46,649 --> 01:23:55,072
And that's why, because there are 4,000 homes that are owner-occupied in this community that would see an increase in the tax bill, not a decrease in the tax bill.

1077
01:23:55,472 --> 01:23:57,273
and with the breakeven of $727,000 a few.

1078
01:23:57,373 --> 01:24:06,055
We're an owner-occupied home owner, say, in East Ford, at a two-family home.

1079
01:24:06,415 --> 01:24:09,576
It sounds like you may actually be above and beyond that breakeven point.

1080
01:24:09,696 --> 01:24:13,357
